00:50:17.190 --> 00:50:21.820
and as well as simply just
like the number of people,

00:50:21.820 --> 00:50:26.370
and perhaps how the
internet has certainly

00:50:26.370 --> 00:50:31.430
fueled innovation in that way--
but perhaps plans on, like,

00:50:31.430 --> 00:50:33.850
expanding.

00:50:33.850 --> 00:50:37.820
For example, going to Mars
and colonizing that as a path

00:50:37.820 --> 00:50:44.134
toward accelerating our
evolution essentially.

00:50:44.134 --> 00:50:45.550
MATT RIDLEY: Well
I really enjoyed

00:50:45.550 --> 00:50:47.020
that book, "The Martian."

00:50:47.020 --> 00:50:49.580
And I enjoyed the
movie, too, but I

00:50:49.580 --> 00:50:52.440
