It likes to kind of
pretend it's in charge,

00:56:56.670 --> 00:56:58.120
but I'm not sure it really is.

00:57:01.360 --> 00:57:03.410
In other words, I'm
sort of slightly

00:57:03.410 --> 00:57:05.090
saying to you that
I think you're still

00:57:05.090 --> 00:57:08.720
falling for a top
down view, which

00:57:08.720 --> 00:57:10.180
isn't correct of these things.

00:57:10.180 --> 00:57:12.489
But yes, standards
do have to emerge.

00:57:12.489 --> 00:57:13.780
There's no question about that.

00:57:13.780 --> 00:57:16.350
But I think that the internet
standards have emerged

00:57:16.350 --> 00:57:17.435
